<HEADLINE> Russian Military Delegation Visits Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, January 19 (Xinhua) -- The visit by a Russian high-level
military delegation to Vietnam would help promote traditional
friendship and comprehensive cooperation between armies of the two
countries, a senior Vietnamese official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese Defence Minister Pham Van Tra made the remark when
meeting Russian First Deputy Defense Minister A.V. Kvasnin, who
headed a military delegation arriving here for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
The Russian delegation is expected to hold talks later in the
day with Vietnamese Major General Dao Trong Lich and other
high-ranking officers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
