<HEADLINE> France Hopes U.S. Can Relaunch Mideast Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 19 (Xinhua) -- France Monday expressed hope that
United States President Bill Clinton can relaunch the Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
Talking about the coming visits to Washington by Israeli Prime
Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat,
French Foreign Ministry spokeswoman, Anne Gazeau-Secret, said
France hopes the United States "can obtain positive results" and
that the peace process can be relaunched.
</P>
<P>
Arafat is scheduled to make a stopover in Paris Tuesday on his
way to Washington and will meet with President Jacques Chirac,
said the spokeswoman.
</P>
<P>
Arafat will also sign an agreement in Paris with the World Bank
on the establishment of a fund of one million U.S. dollars for the
development of the West Bank and Gaza Strip. 
</P>
</TEXT>
