<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Call on to Protect and Promote Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 19 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today called on the international society to make
greater efforts to protect and promote human rights.
</P>
<P>
In his remarks to the Martin Luther King Day, January 19,
Annan said this year marks the 50th anniversary of the Universal
Declaration of Human Rights, which had been a fundamental source
of inspiration for national and international efforts to protect
and promote human rights and freedom.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary-General said the main principles of the
Declaration have inspired the constitutions of many countries which
have become independent since it was written.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief said conceived as a "common standard of
achievement for all peoples and nations", the Declaration has
become a yardstick by which to measure the respect for, and
compliance with, international human rights standards.
</P>
<P>
Annan stressed human rights are African rights. They are also
Asian rights; they are European rights; they are American rights.
They belong to no government, they are limited to no continent,
for they are fundamental to humankind itself. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
