<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreigners Active in S. African Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Foreigners were net
purchasers of 1.4 billion Rand (280 million U.S. Dollars) on
South Africa's stock market in the calendar year ending January
16, 1998, the Johannesburg Stock Exchange (JSE) said today.
</P>
<P>
This was a significant leap from the 83.93 million Rand (16.79
million Dollars) in the corresponding period in 1997, the
industrialists said.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners invested 1.54 billion Rand (308 million Dollars)
and sold shares worth 814.71 million Rand (162.94 million
Dollars) in the week ending January 16, 1998, the JSE said.
</P>
<P>
The weekly purchases were also a significant leap from the
837.05 million Rand (167.41 million Dollars) purchased by the
foreigners in the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Net purchases for the week ending January 16 1998 were 727.27
million Rand (145.46 million Dollars) compared to 108.15 million
Rand (21.63 million Dollars) in the week ending January 17, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Purchases in the calendar year up to January 16, surged to
2.84 billion Rand (568 million Dollars) compared to the 2.1
billion Rand (420 million Dollars) in the corresponding period in
1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
