<HEADLINE> Egyptian, Arab Funds Sign Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Two funds of Egypt and the Arab
League (AL) Monday signed a cooperation agreement in the fields
of agriculture and irrigation, the Middle East News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, a training course in agriculture will be
held here in September within the framework of south-south
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa and AL Secretary General
Ahmed Esmat Abdel-Meguid signed the agreement representing the
Egyptian Fund for Technical Cooperation with Africa under the
Foreign Ministry and AL's Arab Fund for Cooperation with Africa.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Moussa said the agreement is an
important event for promoting cooperation between the two funds.
</P>
<P>
He underlined the importance of the agreement, saying it is "a
base for south-south cooperation."
</P>
<P>
It will also lead to Afro-Arab cooperation in vital issues in
the two regions, he added.
</P>
<P>
Abdel-Meguid said the agreement is a step forward to serve the
joint actions of Arab and African countries. 
</P>
