<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Plans to Hike Meat, Hide Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopian Deputy Prime
Minister Kassu Ilala announced here that the country has plans
this year to launch a program aimed at boosting its meat and hide
and skin export to the international market.
</P>
<P>
According to a today's report from the Ethiopian News Agency,
Kassu said Ethiopia's meat export is very low quantity-wise and the
volume of hide and skin enters the foreign market is insignificant.
</P>
<P>
He said his Horn of African states' share in the 17 billion
U.S. Dollars worth of meat supplied to the world market last year
was only 0.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The new initiative is hoped to promote the country's access to
the world and particularly the Middle East market, he said, and
added that the government has plans to increase fodder supply and
improve the species of the cattle with the loan obtained from the
African Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia stands first in Africa and 10th in the world in its
livestock resource. Hide and skin export is second largest export
item in the country next to coffee. 
</P>
