<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-19 19:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 F-15Is Delivered to Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, January 19 (Xinhua) -- The first two of 25
U.S.-made F-15I long-range strike aircrafts arrived in Israel
Monday in a high-profile welcome aimed at showcasing its
technological superiority and deterrence.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Yitzhak Mordechai attended the welcome
ceremony held at the Hatzerim Air Force Base in southern
Israel. The planes, code-named Thunder, are the most advanced and
expensive jets in Israel's arsenal.
</P>
<P>
Using the annual military aid of 1.8 billion dollars from the
United States, Israel has purchased 25 F-15Is from Boeing company
in a deal worth 2.5 billion dollars. The last will be delivered by
the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The jets were officially handed over to Israel at the rolling
out ceremony in St. Louis, United States, last November and
Israeli crews have been under training in the U.S. for the past
six months.
</P>
<P>
The F-15I has a range of at least 4,500 kilometers and can
carry 11 tonnes of missiles and bombs. It is able to reach any
target in the Middle East, fight in any kind of weather, day or
night, and carry a variety of weapons and bombs. It is also a
strategic bomber that is quite capable of engaging the enemy in
dog fights.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Air Force Commander Eitan Ben Eliyahu said once the
F-15Is become operational, Israeli air forces can carry out
missions that could not be done in the past.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that, as the F-15Is are equipped with advanced
avionics, precision guided weaponry, and enlarged fuel tanks,
they enable Israel to strike targets as far as Iraq, Iran and
Libya without refueling. The three countries are top rivals in the
region which Israel considers as leading military threats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980120.0037 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-19 19:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Criticizes US for Arming Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Iran Monday criticized the
United States for arming Israel "in an excessive way," the Iranian
official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi said
that Israel's military build-up is "dangerous to the Middle
East," calling on Muslim countries to stop remaining indifferent
towards Washington's military support for Israel's expansionist
policies.
</P>
<P>
The annual military aid from the United States to Israel now
stands at 1.8 billion U.S. dollars. The first two of 25 U.S.-made
F-15I long-range strike aircraft arrived in Israel Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said that to divert public opinion in the region from
Israel's military build-up, the U.S. has launched baseless
propaganda campaign against Iran by accusing Tehran of purchasing
long-range missiles from China and Russia.
</P>
<P>
The United States repeatedly accused Iran of seeking weapons
of mass destruction and some U.S. military officials even claimed
that Tehran has got access to long-range missiles, with which
Iran can attack Israeli targets.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi stressed that Iran has based its regional policy
of detente on ridding the Middle East region of weapons of
mass destruction, saying that Iran called on Muslim countries
to put pressure on Israel to accept supervision of the
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). 
</P>
</TEXT>
