<P>
LAGOS, January 19 (Xinhua) -- The fate of the ambassadors of
the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) suspended last June by the
new administration of Laurent Kabila, are yet to know, the News
Agency of Nigeria reported today.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after assuming leadership of DRC on May 17, Kabila
instructed all ambassadors appointed by the government of the
late Mobutu Sese Seko to hand over the affairs of the embassies
to their immediate subordinates.
</P>
<P>
