handed over his power to the charge d'affairs although he still
lives in his official residence.
</P>
<P>
It said that all the embassy staff, diplomats and
non-diplomats alike, including the local staff, have not been
paid salaries for seven years.
</P>
<P>
A Nigerian staff of the embassy was quoted as saying that "my
wife has been supporting me but I believe they will pay."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Lignes Aeriennes Congolaises (LAC), formerly called
Zaire Airways, has resumed flights from Kinshasa to Lagos.
</P>
<P>
LAC suspended flights to Nigeria in 1995 and resumed on
December 1 last year. 
