<HEADLINE> Turkey Slams Greece for Discriminating Ethnic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Turkey on Monday criticized
Greece for its discriminative attitude toward the ethnic Turks on
citizenship issue, describing it as "unacceptable."
</P>
<P>
Addressing a weekly news briefing here, Turkish Foreign
Ministry spokesman Necati Utkan said that the new Greek
citizenship law would harm the interests of the Turks living in
the Greek province of Western Thrace.
</P>
<P>
Under the 19th article of the citizenship law, those Greek
citizens without Greek extraction will be stripped of their
citizenship if they leave Greece for permanent residence abroad.
</P>
<P>
Utkan said that the Greek move proved that it based
citizenship on ethnic background.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that Greece will amend its legislation and introduce
new rules with no discrimination based on ethnic origin," he added.
</P>
<P>
Around 150,000 ethnic Turks are now living in Western
Thrace. Turkey has repeatedly accused Greece of taking a
discriminative attitude toward them. 
</P>
