<HEADLINE> Clinton Deplores Incident in Guatemala </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 19 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
today deplored the incident in which the Guatemalan gunmen robbed
and assaulted a group of American college students in Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
"I have a lot of concern, obviously, for the victims and their
families," Clinton told reporters while he helped renovate a local
high school at a King Day service project. "It's a terrible
thing," he added.
</P>
<P>
Clinton also expressed his confidence that the Guatemalan
government is taking "appropriate action."
</P>
<P>
On Friday, a bus carrying 16 students and teachers from St.
Mary's College in Maryland was ambushed by a group of gunmen on an
isolated Guatemalan highway. Five women were raped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
