<HEADLINE> Belgium Imposes Ban on German Pigs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Belgium said today it was
banning all imports of pigs from Germany where more than 80,000
animals had been slaughtered due to two recent outbreaks of
classic swine fever.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here today, Belgian Farm Minister Karel
Pinxten said the ban, which would go into effect at midnight, was
aimed at hindering the highly infectious disease from crossing
into Belgium.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to all pig farmers in the country who had imported
German pigs lately to be on alert to any signs of the disease
developing.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU)'s veterinary authorities are scheduled
to discuss the swine fever outbreak Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An aide to EU Farm Commissioner Franz Fischler said an export
ban was possible if Germany failed to control the outbreak by
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
