<HEADLINE> 1 Killed, 3 Wounded in Gunfire at King Day Parade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 19 (Xinhua) -- One person was killed and
three others were wounded when gunshots were fired into a crowd of
marchers at a parade honoring U.S. civil rights leader Martin
Luther King Jr. at Baton Rouge, Louisiana, today, said media
reports.
</P>
<P>
A 25-year-old black man was shot to death and three children
were wounded. The wounded children were a six-year-old girl and an
11-year-old girl, who were listed in serious condition with
gunshot wounds, and a nine-year-old boy, who was listed as stable
with a leg wound.
</P>
<P>
Police were searching for at least one shooter, who was
believed to be black, Don Kelly, a police spokesman, was quoted as
saying. The motive was not immediately clear. 
