<HEADLINE> China Develops Automatic Collector for Seabed Sediments </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- China has developed its first
automatic collector for seabed sediments, analysis of which
provides data for research into its source, movement and
pollution to the environment.
</P>
<P>
The No. 1 Oceanic Research Institute under the State Oceanic
Administration applied advanced space technologies to develop the
collector, which is propelled by hydraulic pressure instead of the
popularly-applied electrical machinery driving system.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of tests had been conducted on the instrument before
two field experiments, which respectively took place in a port
and the continental shelf of the East China Sea.
</P>
<P>
During the two field tests, the collector dived 140 meters
deep, and 13 of its sampling bottles were filled with collected
sediments, when it came back out of the water.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980120.0079 </DOCNO>
