Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee, extended new year's greetings
to more than 2,000 retired officials who gathered in a reception
at the Great Hall of the People here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the reception, Hu stressed that Party officials at
all levels should put people's interests foremost and should not
cut themselves off from the masses.
</P>
<P>
At present, leading officials should help address problems
facing laid-off workers, the retired and the poor, Hu said, and
concern themselves with the well-being of these people.
</P>
