<HEADLINE> Top Leaders Show Concern for Tibetans Hit by Snowstorm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice Premier Jiang
Chunyun today urged governments at all levels to spare no effort
in supporting the fight against the effects of a severe snowstorm
that hit Nagqu in the Tibet Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
"We must work to ensure the safety of all those hit by the
snowstorm, and create necessary conditions for post-storm
rebuilding of the area," Jiang told a group that just returned
from Nagqu in north Tibet, where they conveyed the solicitude of
central authorities to local people.
</P>
<P>
Since the storm hit the area last month, Chinese president
Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng repeatedly have concerned
themselves with conditions in the disaster area. A special group
was dispatched by the central authorities on Jan. 7 to help with
disaster relief in Nagqu.
</P>
<P>
Recognizing the great difficulties of disaster relief in a
high-altitude area such as Nagqu, Jiang called for governments at
all levels to boost their confidence in fighting the disaster.
</P>
<P>
He also voiced his belief that, with the correct leadership and
deep concern of the central authorities as well as support from
across the nation, people affected by the snowstorm are bound to
overcome the disaster. 
</P>
