<HEADLINE> Dhaka Gets ADB Loans for Developing Cellular Phone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
said Tuesday that it had approved a 30 million U.S. dollars loan
and a 1.6 million equity investment for the construction and
operation of a nationwide cellular telephone system in Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
The system will provide common cellular services in
Bangladesh's main cities and a village pay telephone service in
its rural areas, the Manila-based multilateral bank said in a
press release.
</P>
<P>
The project will be the first significant private investment in
the country in the telecommunications sector which is
underdeveloped and has a high level of unmet demand, the bank
said.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan and equity investment covers the first four years
of investment and operations, after which the project will become
self-financing.  
