<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Martina
Hingis breezed into the second round of the Australian Open
Wednesday after routing German Wiltrud Probst 6-1, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Hingis has often used the early rounds in grand slams as a time
to experiment and the World No.1 saw no reason to change after
collecting three major titles last year.
</P>
<P>
