<HEADLINE> ADB Approves Loans for Agricultural Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
Tuesday approved a total of 7.3 million U.S. dollar technical
assistance grant to conduct agricultural research in the Asian and
Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Among the total technical assistance grant, 5.5 million dollars
will be used to study ways to increase the productivity of major
agricultural products and fish stocks in the region, the
Manila-based bank said in a news release.
</P>
<P>
Four studies will be undertaken to develop specific
intervention and promote sustainable management of agriculture and
natural resources, in support of the bank's agenda in the region.
</P>
<P>
The studies will deal with the application of biotechnology to
maize improvement, sustainable management of coastal fish stocks,
coconut genetic resources network and human resources
strengthening and the development and use of hybrid rice in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The rest 1.8 million dollar technical assistance will be used
to review developments in the rural economies of the region over
the last two decades and provide a vision for the future of
agriculture and rural development, the ADB said.  
</P>
