<DOCNO> XIE19980120.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thousands of French Teachers Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of teachers
across France went on a strike Tuesday to protest about unequal
pay for teachers.
</P>
<P>
The protesting teachers are "instituteurs" who are older and
who are categorized by the government as state employees.
</P>
<P>
They claim that they are paid less than "professeurs d'ecoles,"
their colleagues who are younger, college trained license holders.
</P>
<P>
The strikers say they should be paid the same as the
professeurs d'ecole, because both are doing the same job in front
of the same kids.
</P>
<P>
But the government has set a quota for the number of
instituteurs and professseurs d'ecole, because an overall
integration of the two groups would cost billions of francs.
</P>
<P>
The union which represents the instituteurs said that half the
teachers were on strike Tuesday, in 75 percent of the departments
registered with the union. 
</P>
</TEXT>
