<HEADLINE> Thailand to Set up Bank to Dispose of Finance Firms' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet Tuesday
approved the Finance Ministry's proposal on the establishment of a
commercial bank, a finance company and a securities company to
dispose of assets of the 56 finance companies permanently closed
down last December.
</P>
<P>
The three new financial institutions will play an important
role in the bidding process of assets to be put for auction of the
56 closed finance companies, according to a Government House press
release.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry will be the major shareholder of the new
commercial bank, to be named Radhanasin Bank PCL. Its initial
capital will be 4 billion baht (75.5 million US dollars), which
comes from the Structural Adjustment Loan of the World Bank and
the Asian Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
At the initial stage, the Finance Ministry will also be the
major shareholder of both the finance company and the securities
company. The two companies will be the new commercial bank's
subsidiaries.
</P>
<P>
The Finance Ministry said in its proposal that the
establishment of the three new financial institutions will be a
major step in solving the problems of the country's financial
sector and in restoring confidence of both domestic and foreign
investors in the Thai financial system.  
</P>
</TEXT>
