the company would default 39 million HK dollars (5 million U.S.
dollars) to the Central Clearing and Settlement System.
</P>
<P>
Financial Secretary of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (SAR) Donald Tsang said Tuesday: "The operations are normal
and well supervised, and all the cash clients of the company are
well protected."
</P>
<P>
The provisional liquidators are two persons from Coopers &AMP;
Lybrand.
</P>
<P>
The SFC said in a press release, "The priority task of the
liquidators is to process claims by clients of the company as
expeditiously as possible." Their appointment will not affect the
sale of the business.  
