<HEADLINE> Bombay Stock Market Index Loses 24.91 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday lost 24.91 points to
3455.95 as against Monday's close of 3480.86.
</P>
<P>
The National index also dropped by 10.76 points to 1505.90 from
previous close of 1516.66.
</P>
<P>
Equities turned subdued in narrow movements as prices failed to
sustain their higher levels on the BSE market Tuesday due to
profit booking by financial institutions and bull operators.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said that the Asian markets could not have much impact
on the Indian bourses Tuesday as foreign institutional investors
stayed off with directionless trend in the Southeast Asian stocks.
</P>
<P>
</P>
