<HEADLINE> China to Host Rare Earth Beijing 98' </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Rare Earth Beijing 98' is to be
held here in Beijing Exhibition Center in October 5-10 this year
to show the latest development of the world rare earth industry.
</P>
<P>
Li Jian, an official with the industry department of the State
Science and Technology Commission, announced here at a news
conference that China will encourage the establishment of
overseas-funded rare earth ventures.
</P>
<P>
He said that China also plans to introduce advanced technology
and equipment for rare earth application in the form of
compensation trade.
</P>
<P>
Li added that China has launched rare earth development
programs with Japan, France and Australia. The European Union has
also expressed its wishes to strengthen cooperation with China in
the rare earth field.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Chuandian, chairman of the China Society of Rare Earth, said
the international exhibition will be jointly sponsored by the
State Science and Technology Commission, State Planning Commission
and Ministry of Metallurgy.
</P>
<P>
Li Jian said rare earth has been playing an important role in
China's economic growth and national defense industry. China's
proved rare earth reserve accounts for nearly 80 percent of the
world's total.
</P>
<P>
Li said 66 Chinese rare earth ventures are producing some 300
varieties of rare earth products and 60 percent of China's rare
earth products are exported abroad annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
