<HEADLINE> World's Largest Electrolytic Manganese Dioxide Producer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Xiangtan Electrochemical
Group Company in Xiangtan, central China's Hunan Province, has an
annual production capacity of 25,000 tons of electrolytic
manganese dioxide and is believed to be the largest producer of
the product in the world.
</P>
<P>
Since May 1997, the group has allocated some 50 million yuan
for projects to increase output, with the completion of related
projects increasing the annual production capacity to the present
level.
</P>
<P>
The group, the largest company of its kind in China, accounts
for 70 percent of the country's total output of electrolytic
manganese dioxide. 
