<HEADLINE> Beijing University's High-Tech Ventures Grow Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Beijing University, one of
China's top five universities in terms of scientific research, has
received an annual output of more than 6 billion yuan (720 million
U.S. dollars) from its 47 high-tech ventures.
</P>
<P>
Li Pingfang, a official in charge of the university's high-tech
ventures, said most of them are engaged in the information,
pharmaceutical, chemical and real estate sectors.
</P>
<P>
Beijing University Founders Group had an output and trade value
of 5.85 billion yuan (700 million U.S. dollars) in 1997. Its
Chinese-language electronic publication system and computer
software are selling well.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Univerity Weiming Biological Group has several
foreign-funded centers. The group develops and produces
gene-engineering vaccines, diagnostic reagents and agro-biology
products.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Kexing Biological Products Corp., a branch of the
group, ranks at the top of China's gene-engineering pharmaceutical
bases, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The university also established a joint venture with Singapore
to produce drugs for reducing blood-fat.
</P>
<P>
Li said the growth of the university's high-tech ventures
benefited from scientific discoveries made by state-level labs and
research institutions of the university, and that the ventures
also funded those labs and institutions in return. 
</P>
</TEXT>
