<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gold Prices in India Continue Slidedown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Gold prices in India
continued to lean down on the bullion market Tuesday in the wake
of persistent inflow of supply against any worthwhile buying
support.
</P>
<P>
Market men said that some offering of gold in the market by
importers in the absence of buying activity created easy
availability of the commodity. Though gold prices in Hong Kong
market were up at 288.25 U.S. dollars an ounce on short-covering,
it failed to impact the markets here.
</P>
<P>
Standard gold and ornaments dropped by 85 rupees (2.30 U.S.
dollars) each at 4,015 and 3,865 rupees (108.51-104.46 U.S.
dollars) per 10 gram, respectively.
</P>
<P>
However, sovereign gained by 25 rupees at 3,550 (95.95 U.S.
dollars) per piece of eight gram on scattered buying by local
parties.
</P>
<P>
In restricted movements on small bouts of buying and selling,
silver maintained its previous level.  
</P>
</TEXT>
