<HEADLINE> Shanghai Standardizes Pharmaceutical Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai pricing authorities
recently decided to establish a specialized department to
standardize prices for pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
Since April 1997, the city has reduced prices of 106
pharmaceutical products and increased charges for medical
services.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Pricing Bureau also introduced ceiling prices for
various pharmaceuticals and introduced regulations prohibiting
hospitals from changing these prices, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Three new associations will set prices for most domestically
manufactured pharmaceutical products.
</P>
<P>
The bureau plans to regularly announce retail prices for 2,200
products via the mass media. Additional changes will also be
introduced between now and March, according to officials.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai residents have often complained about random price
hikes for pharmaceuticals in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
