<HEADLINE> Medical Team Sent to Snow-hit Nagqu in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The government of Tibet
Autonomous Region today dispatched the first medical team to Nagqu
County which has been hit by a snowstorm.
</P>
<P>
Carrying with it 660,000 yuan worth of medicines, the
26-member team is from the region's No. 1 and No. 2 people's
hospitals, and the hospitals of the Chinese PLA and Chinese
People's Armed Police units stationed in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Just after the serious snowstorm in Nagqu, the region's
department of health sent groups of officials to visit victims of
the disaster. Those seriously injured have been treated
immediately.
</P>
<P>
However, many victims are still suffering from snow blindness,
cold injuries, diarrhea and flu, and the team will first treat
those who have suffered most. 
</P>
</TEXT>
