<HEADLINE> Uganda President to Attend Arusha Seminar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni will leave here tomorrow to attend a workshop in Arusha
of Tanzania to deal with conflict and peace in Africa, informed
sources told Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
Hope Kwengere, the Press Secretary to the President, said the
meeting will last one or two days on the theme of "conflict
resolution and building in Africa."
</P>
<P>
Museveni will release a key note adress at the workshop
initiated by Mwalimu Nyerere Foundation and organized in
collaboration with the Tanzanian foreign ministry.
</P>
<P>
Julius Nyerere, the former Tanzanian President, will be the
main speaker at the workshop.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Butiku, the Executive Director of the Mwalimu Nyerere
Foundation, said in Dar es Salaam that the workshop will review
previous and current conflict resolution efforts in Africa,
especially in Burundi, according to a report reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The occasion will draw participants from beyond Africa but
Burundi has been given a special allocation and would field a
number of delegates, Butiku explained.  
</P>
