<HEADLINE> Malaysian, Singapore PMs Discuss Regional Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad met his Singapore counterpart Goh Chok Tong
Tuesday and discussed with him on the regional currency crisis and
bilateral relations, the Malaysian national news agency Bernama
reported.
</P>
<P>
The 90-minute meeting between the two leaders took place at the
Sebana Resort, about 140 kilometers from Johor Baharu in southern
Malaysia, the report said.
</P>
