<HEADLINE> China Forms Joint Bank for Railway Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank of
China (SDB) and some commercial banks have formed a joint bank to
provide funding for the construction of a railway for coal
transportation in north China.
</P>
<P>
The joint bank, led by SDB and its leading agent, the Beijing
branch of the China Construction Bank, one of the country's
big-four state-owned commercial banks, is meant to ensure the
supply of funds for the railway.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the 600-km-long Shuohuang Railway, which links
Shuozhou of Shanxi Province and Huanghua of Hebei Province,
involves a total investment of 16.6 billion yuan and is expected
to complete in 2003.
</P>
<P>
The SDB, a policy-oriented bank set up in 1994 to fund the
construction of large projects, has agreed to extend 6.4 billion
yuan in loans for the railway project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
