<HEADLINE> Hebei Improves Labor Market System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 20 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province had invested 200 million yuan by the end of last month to
establish 1,700 employment agencies.
</P>
<P>
Over 3,000 labor service centers have also been introduced by
all neighborhood committees in urban districts and townships in
rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The employment agencies distribute job information, offer
training courses and provide consulting services.
</P>
<P>
More than 1.2 million unemployed people have registered with
related agencies over the past two years. Some 900,000 people, or
75 percent of registrants, have found new jobs.
</P>
<P>
Over 500 professionals exchange fairs were held in 1997, with
some 26,000 participants finding new jobs.  
</P>
</TEXT>
