<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Set to Become China's Stone Materials Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region is making great efforts to become the country's
major stone materials production base during the next decade.
</P>
<P>
The region has abundant oil, gold and other mineral resources,
as well as abundant reserves of stone in the Tianshan, Kunlun and
Altay mountain ranges.
</P>
<P>
Extensive stone reserves are found in more than half of the
region's 84 counties, with 110 marble and granite quarries
offering verified reserves of 1.2 billion cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang has the capacity to process more than one million
cubic meters of stone plates annually, with the capacity expected
to increase by as much as 10-fold by the year 2010. The
corresponding output value is expected to rise to 1.8 billion yuan
and export volume to 35 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The region's stone processing industry, which was established
in 1978, now includes 62 stone quarries and 42 processing
plants. The industry markets 30 varieties of stone products on
both domestic and overseas markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
