<HEADLINE> Heilongjiang Expands Trade Cooperation With Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The government of Heilongjiang
Province, which shares a 3,045-km border line with Russia, has
introduced a plan to strengthen economic and trade cooperation
with Russia during 1998.
</P>
<P>
The province, which is home to abundant timber, coal, oil and
natural gas resources, will expand bilateral cooperation in areas
such as timbering, oil extraction, the cultivation of farm produce
and labor exports.
</P>
<P>
The plan also calls for expanded cooperation to upgrade the
technology and equipment of state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang will also participate in developing natural
resources in Russia and will explore opportunities for cooperation
in other fields.
</P>
<P>
The borders cities of Heihe and Suifenhe will become export
production bases for foodstuffs, fodder, textiles, garments, farm
produce and durable consumer goods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
