<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 20 (Xinhua) -- A total of 401 Macao residents
applied to enter China's inland universities for post-graduate and
doctorate degrees in 1998, an increase of 55 percent over that in
1997.
</P>
<P>
Figures released on Tuesday by the Macao Foundation, which
assists China's State Education Commission for the recruitment in
Macao, showed that they are applying to enter 31 universities in
China's inland areas.
</P>
