<HEADLINE> Taiwan Political Figures' Trips to Southeast Asia Denounced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry
spokesman Shen Guofang today told a news briefing that China hopes
Southeast Asian countries concerned will maintain vigilance
against the political motives of the Taiwan authorities and
properly handle their relations with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that some political figures of Taiwan have recently
made frequent trips to some countries in Southeast Asia and
conducted activities there, capitalizing on the temporary
difficulties of these countries caused by the financial crisis and
carrying out "pragmatic diplomacy" in this region in an attempt to
realize their set political motivations.
</P>
<P>
He noted that those figures claimed to revive the "policy of
advancing South" and demanded in explicit terms for "political
reward" from these southeast Asian countries for Taiwan's
financial assistance and financial cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Evidently, this is a well-planned and premeditated political
move which is aimed at upgrading Taiwan's so-called 'substantive
relationship' with Southeast Asian countries and furthermore
undermining the friendly relations and cooperation between China
and the countries concerned," he said.
</P>
<P>
"What the Taiwan authorities have done is unpopular and doomed
to failure," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman reiterated that there is only one China in the
world, and the government of the People's Republic of China is the
sole legal government representing the whole China, and Taiwan is
an inalienable part of the Chinese territory.
</P>
<P>
The position of the Chinese government on the question of
Taiwan is consistent, clear-cut, firm and unshakable, he added.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the Chinese government understands the
special difficulties and predicament of some Southeast Asian
countries and therefore takes no objection to the non-governmental
economic contacts and trade between the countries concerned and
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"However, we are resolutely opposed to any form of official
contacts with Taiwan by countries having diplomatic relations with
China," Shen said.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will never do anything which jeopardizes the
interests of the countries concerned who are at the moment still
caught in a difficult position.
</P>
<P>
"We urge countries concerned to respect the position of China,
strictly honor their commitment to the 'one China' policy and
jointly maintain the overall interests of their friendship and
cooperation with China, so that the friendship and cooperation
will continue to forge ahead in a healthy and steady manner," the
spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
