<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> School Drop-outs in Guizhou Resume Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,024 drop-outs in
southwest China's Guizhou Province have resumed their education
thanks to donations from Shenzhen, one of the country's first
special economic zones.
</P>
<P>
The students, half of whom belong to Shui Ethnic Group, live in
the Sandu Shui Autonomous County, a poverty-stricken mountainous
area in Guizhou.
</P>
<P>
The government of Shenzhen, south China's Guangdong Province,
has raised a total of 13.3 million yuan in educational donations
since 1995 to help poverty-stricken children in the county return
to school.
</P>
<P>
The donations have been used to build 21 primary schools and
provide assistance to over 8,000 local students.  
</P>
</TEXT>
