<HEADLINE> Stocks Rise Fifth Day in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Tokyo stock prices advanced for
five tradings in a row Tuesday on continued expectations of
additional economic stimulus measures.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei average of 225 selected issues on the First Section
of the Tokyo Stock Exchange Tuesday climbed 104.49 points, or 0.64
percent from Monday's close to 16,366.53.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
issues on the First Section, added 1.43 points, or 0.12 percent to
1,232.89.
</P>
<P>
Volume on the First Section came to an estimated 570 million
shares, down from Monday's 680.28 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Nippon Steel was Tuesday's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Although there were few strong buying incentives, the benchmark
Nikkei index continued to rise as buying by foreign investors and
arbitragers overcame selling in the wake of a 1,600 point rise in
the previous four trading days, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Market participants are hoping the government will unveil even
more economic stimulus measures before the end of the current
business year, they said.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,328 issues listed on the First Section, gainers
outpaced losers 758 to 403 with 131 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
