<HEADLINE> East China Province Records Good Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Despite unfavorable natural
conditions, east China's Anhui Province reaped a good grain
harvest of 28.5 million tons last year, up 5.6 percent on 1996.
</P>
<P>
Cotton output jumped by 11.5 percent to 300,000 tons and the
output of oil-bearing corps increased by 10 percent to reach 1.95
million tons.
</P>
<P>
The per capita net income of local farmers surpassed 1,800
yuan, up 200 yuan on the 1996 level.
</P>
<P>
The good harvest was the result of substantial investments in
agricultural production, local government officials say.
</P>
<P>
The local government has invested nearly 7.7 billion yuan in
agriculture since 1993, with an annual growth rate in agricultural
investment standing at 23 percent.
</P>
<P>
Increased funding has significantly improved the conditions for
local agricultural development and helped transform over 530,000
ha of low-yielding farmland.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of new technology also contributed greatly to
the increased grain output. Hybrid and high-quality seeds have
been introduced to 88 percent of local farmland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
