<HEADLINE> China's Customs Cracks Down on Smuggling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- China's customs uncovered 7,265
smuggling cases involving 6.735 billion yuan last year,
International Business Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
Among all the cases, 1,128 involved more than 300,000 yuan
each, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Smuggled goods include edible oil, chemical fibre, automobiles,
cigarettes, wool, copper and industrial chemicals.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises and institutions were involved in 742 major
smuggling cases which smuggled 5.174 yuan worth of products, it
said.  
</P>
