<HEADLINE> Anhui Experiencing Coldest Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province today
records this winter's coldest morning, with the capital Hefei City
recording temperatures at 10.5 degrees below zero centigrade.
</P>
<P>
This morning's temperature was seventh lowest on record, said
Liu Xiaochang, deputy-director of Anhui Meteorological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Anhui had experienced higher than normal winter temperatures
since October in advance of the first extremely cold spell which
hit on January 13.
</P>
<P>
Snow and ice have since caused great inconvenience to local
residents. Two expressways from downtown Hefei to the local
airport were temporarily closed, and a mere 33 percent of Hefei's
taxi remains in operation.
</P>
<P>
Local governments are attempting to stablize vegetable prices
amidst prevailing shortages on the markets.
</P>
<P>
However, meteorologists note that crops will most likely
benefit from the cold snap. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
