</P>
<P>
Upon his return from Washington to the Lithuanian capital of
Vilnius, Brazauskas said the Charter of Partnership is not a bad
thing for Russia and should not lead to its negative responses.
(Lithuania-US-Baltics)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ZAGREB -- Croatian Foreign Minister Mate Granic met his
Slovenian counterpart Boris Frlec on Monday on improving bilateral
ties and enhancing cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Following their talks in Slovenia, the two top diplomats issued
a joint statement saying they had come to agreement on resolving
some of the disputes between the two former Yugoslav republics.
One of the issues discussed, they said, was the border dispute
along the Piran strait. Although still at odds, they decided to
let exports from both sides to meet and search for a
solution. (Croatia-Slovenia-Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- A small bomb exploded in an apartment building in
Tanah Tinggi, Central Jakarta, on Sunday evening, injuring at
least two people, security authorities and news reports here said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Police said the explosion, which also damaged the apartment
building, was carried out by supporters of the outlawed People's
Democratic Party (PRD). Police arrested several leaders of the PRD
for allegedly masterminding riots on July 27, 1996.
(Indonesia-Explosion)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
