<HEADLINE> East China Province Receives More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 20 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
played host to 585,000 overseas tourists in 1997, a year-on-year
rise of ten percent, a provincial tourism official said today.
</P>
<P>
He said the tourists brought to the province more than 200
million US dollars in foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province received 54.8 million domestic tourists
last year, up 6.5 percent from the number in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The province's tourism sector earned a total of 2.3 billion
yuan (277 million US dollars), according to the official.
</P>
<P>
A favorite tourism destination in the country, Shandong has
made great efforts to develop overseas market. Last year, the
province sent more than sales 100 promotion groups to 24 countries
and regions.
</P>
<P>
The province also invested 5.2 billion yuan on 420 tourism
projects in 1997, which include hotel construction. Currently, it
has 123 star-rated hotels.  
</P>
