<HEADLINE> Uganda-Kenya Highway Reopened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- With the repairing of a bridge
near Malaba near Uganda-Kenya border, Uganda-Kenya highway have
been reopened yesterday, The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
Orioi bridge on Malaba-Tororo road in eastern Uganda damaged
by floods on January 11 caused a jam of over 400 trucks in Malaba
border post.
</P>
<P>
A new six meter long culvert with its diameter of 2.3 meter
has been temporarily installed to sustain the transport.
</P>
<P>
Tororo-Malaba road is the main way linking Uganda and Kenya.
The other way is through Busia border post on Uganda side.
</P>
<P>
With the reopening of Tororo-Malaba road, the highway linking
Kenya with Uganda, Rwanda, Congo and Southern Sudan have been
reopened.
</P>
<P>
The section near Kibwezi on Nairobi-Mombasa have been repaired
Friday, J.G. Mwedde, an engineer in the Ministry of Works,
Transport and Communication confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Uganda-Kenya highway is the key land route to the sea-port for
cargo transport from the related eastern and central Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
