<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets British Foreign Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said today that the establishment and development of long-term,
stable, friendly and cooperative Sino-British relations will not
only be in the fundamental interests of the two countries and
their people, but will also be conducive to Sino-European
cooperation and worldwide peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the remarks this morning during a meeting with
visiting British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his pleasure at once again meeting Cook in
Beijing, and expressed hope that the visit will promote
understanding between the two countries and raise bilateral
relations to a new plateau.
</P>
<P>
Jiang recalled that he and Prince Charles presided over the
June 30 hand over ceremony in Hong Kong, and recounted his talks
with British Prime Minister Tony Blair.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the high-degree of autonomy has been practically
and effectively implemented since Hong Kong's return in line with
the principle of "one country, two systems", and "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) has enjoyed
prosperity and stability, and has withstood various tests,
including adverse influences resulting from the financial crisis
in Southeast Asia, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
The good momentum for the improvement and development of
Sino-British relations continues, said Jiang, adding that the
highly desirable situation is worth treasuring by the two sides.
</P>
<P>
Cook pointed to the smooth transition in Hong Kong, and noted
that both sides should be proud of the successful efforts to
implement the concepts of "one country, two systems" and "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong".
</P>
<P>
Cook said that Hong Kong has been a bridge for the development
of Sino-British relations, rather than an obstacle. He pointed to
the vitality and strength of the Hong Kong economy, and expressed
his belief that Hong Kong will withstand the financial crisis in
southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed to the new international situation and noted that
the common interests of China and Britain are increasing, rather
than decreasing, and that the potential for bilateral cooperation
is expanding, rather than diminishing.
</P>
<P>
Cook expressed hope that the prevailing situation will provide
a new starting point for strengthened bilateral relations between
the two important nations, and added that Britain hopes to develop
wide-ranging cooperation with China.
</P>
<P>
Jiang briefed the British delegation on China's political and
economic situation.
</P>
<P>
Cook stressed that it is very important the Chinese currency
(Renminbi) remains stable and strong in order to maintain Hong
Kong's economic stability and help relevant Asian countries
extricate themselves from financial difficulties at an early
date. 
</P>
</TEXT>
