<DOCNO> XIE19980120.0223 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> African Ports Urged to Be Modernized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 20 (Xinhua) -- African ports should modernize
their operations so as to serve their economies effectively, East
African Standard today quoted Kenyan Minister for Transport and
Communication William Ntimama as saying.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a three-day African Ports seminar opened Monday in
the port city of Mombasa, the minister urged African ports to
adopt modern technology to enable them to compete effectively
with other ports around the world.
</P>
<P>
He noted that as the volume of international trade grows and
larger vessels enter service ports, there is need for efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Ntimama said that the success of African ports would depend on
the quality of service to clients as the demand for a more
efficient service at a lower cost was getting rise.
</P>
<P>
In this regard, he pointed out, "we have to focus our plans on
rehabilitation, expansion and replacement of some of our port
facilities."
</P>
<P>
On the same occasion, Kenya Ports Authority Managing Director,
Lenny Mwangola, said that ports in most African countries are
operated under restrictive conditions due to lack of equipment.
</P>
<P>
It is important to computerize port services and incorporate
modern information technology, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that the challenges facing many African ports ranged
from technological, socio-economic, managerial, ownership, and
education and training.
</P>
<P>
African ports lack well-trained pilots, engineers and other
professionals to ensure quick and efficient delivery of service
as there is lack of well-equipped modern maritime training
institutions, he added.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the seminar is "The Challenges Facing African
Ports in the Next Millennium".
</P>
<P>
The seminar is co-hosted by the Port Management Association of
Eastern and Southern Africa, the Port Management Association of
Western and Central Africa and the International Association of
Ports and Harbors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
