<HEADLINE> Social Insurance Benefits South China Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, the largest
industrial center in south China, has established a comparatively
complete social insurance system in an attempt to improve the
living standards of local workers.
</P>
<P>
Over 3.7 million Guangzhou workers have purchased insurance
policies and more than 64,000 families have benefited from the
insurance system.
</P>
<P>
A local official noted that an increasing number of people are
benefitting from the system which prioritizes the development of
old-age pensions and insurance coverage for the unemployed and
suffering from industrial accidents.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that some 1.1 million workers have pension
policies, and 350,000 retired workers monthly stipends of 430 yuan
from unemployment insurance.
</P>
<P>
The insurance system also covers families living below the
poverty line by providing certificate enabling them to purchase
discounted daily necessities.
</P>
<P>
The official noted that the city's unemployment rate is under
2.5 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
