<HEADLINE> Beijing Treats Pollution in Key Industrial Pollution Sources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- A program to treat 50 key
industrial pollution sources in Beijing, the Chinese capital, has
greatly improved environment quality in affected areas,
according to the the Municipal Environmental Protection Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The program has involved suspending operations, relocating,
merging and introducing technical renovations to polluting
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The municipal government invested 104 million yuan (13 million
US dollars) to construct a new suburban factory for the Beijing
Bituminous Concrete Plant. Relocation of the plant, previously
located in downtown Beijing, has greatly reduced noise and dust
emissions in the former area.
</P>
<P>
The new plant is equipped with pollution treatment equipment
which effectively reduces emissions.
</P>
<P>
In addition, China Aerospace Industrial Corporation raised
funds from both state and regional governments to build waste
water treatment plant with a daily capacity of 8,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The plant can effectively treat waste water discharged by more
than 60 factories in a five sq.km. area.  
</P>
