<P>
At the three-day seminar on the Peace Support Operation opened
here Monday, Francis Muhaura, Executive Secretary of the East
African Co-operation (EAC), welcomed the initiative for military
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that peace and stability were the basic ingredients in
economic and social advancement in the East African region.
</P>
<P>
The EAC official noted that the defence departments in the
three countries could forge cooperation in areas such as exchange
of visits, regular meetings of defense chiefs, joint training,
joint exercises, promotion of various joint cultural activities
and seminars.
</P>
<P>
Kenya's Chief of General Staff, General Daudi Tonje, told the
meeting that joint military initiatives were a growing industry
in the new world order and the region should not be left behind.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the cooperation might eventually lead to
integration of the armed forces of the three sister countries.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is a follow-up to a similar meeting held last
November in Arusha, Northern Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
