<HEADLINE> Sichuan Popularizes Advanced Farming Techniques </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Sciences and technologies have
played an important role in agricultural production in southwest
China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
The province allocates over 430 million yuan (53.7 million
U.S. dollars) annually for the popularization of advanced farming
techniques in the province. Over the past two years alone, the
province has introduced 133 new farming techniques.
</P>
<P>
The province has also used improved crop varieties on 33
million hectares of land.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the province's annual agricultural output was
valued at two billion yuan (250 million U.S. dollars) and its
annual grain output increased by 700 million kilograms. 
</P>
