<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Move Tamil Inmates to Barracks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 20 (Xinhua) -- A large number of Tamil
prisoners, including many rebel suspects, in the Kalutara New
Prison in southern Sri Lanka are to be transferred to the Boossa
military detention barracks further south, government officials
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The officials said the Boossa barracks will be exclusively used
to hold Tamil prisoners. The transfer will take place early next
month once the facilities in Boossa are ready to accommodate the
Tamils.
</P>
<P>
The decision to transfer the Tamil prisoners followed a riot
that erupted at the Kalutara New Prison last December, which led
to the deaths of two Tamil inmates and one Muslim.
</P>
<P>
Prison authorities had complained that at the time of the
incident prison guards were unable to stop the clash between the
Sinhala and Tamil inmates as they didn't have proper equipment
like tear gas, rubber bullets and shields to deal with such a
situation.
</P>
<P>
The officials said the Army will be in charge of outer security
of the Boossa barracks while the inner facilities will be run by
the Prisons Department.  
</P>
</TEXT>
