<HEADLINE> New Area of China's Largest Offshore Oilfield Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The J-block of the Suizhong
36-1 oilfield in China's Bohai Sea has just gone into operation.
</P>
<P>
The Suizhong is the country's largest offshore
oilfield. Located at the Liaodong Bay, it covers an area of 43
sq. km. and has more than 300 million tons of proven oil reserves.
</P>
<P>
On the southern tip of the Suizhong oilfield, the newly developed
J-block covers an area of 1.9 sq. km with 16 million
tons of proven reserves. With 16 wells, the block is expected to
have an annual output of 330,000 tons of crude. 
</P>
