<HEADLINE> Vehicle Sales in Thailand Down 38.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Total vehicle sales last year
fell by 38.4 percent to 363,156 units from 589,126 in the previous
year, according to a local press report Thursday.
</P>
<P>
All major car makers suffered declines in sales, ranging from
Honda's 12.4 percent to Kia's staggering 61.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Despite the fall, last year's sales surpassed the pessimistic
target of 360,000 units amid widespread concern among the private
sector and the government that the economic crisis would drive
sales down.
</P>
<P>
Monthly sales in the fourth quarter were significantly down. In
December sales fell 73.9 percent to 15,170 units, in October 73.3
percent and in November 73.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
Sales in each segment shrank last year with passenger cars
falling 23.5 percent from 1996 to 132,060 units, commercial
vehicles dropping 44.5 percent to 231,096 units and one-ton
pick-up trucks plummeting 42.5 percent to 188,324 units.  
</P>
</TEXT>
