<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980120.0275 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Petrochemical Giant Sets Record in Foreign Trade Volume </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The Yangtze Petrochemical
Corp., a petrochemical giant in Nanjing, capital of east China's
Jiangsu Province, set a record 207 million US dollars in foreign
trade volume in 1997 .
</P>
<P>
The company ranked first amongst the province's state-run
industrial enterprises with the right to conduct foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume included exports of 107 million US dollars and
imports of over 100 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The success was attributed to the company's efforts to make
full use of overseas petroleum to overcome domestic shortages.
</P>
<P>
The company imported more than one million tons of crude oil in
1997, some 200,000 tons of which was processed for export.
</P>
<P>
Yangtze Petrochemical attaches great importance to increasing
its share in the foreign market. Some 13 percent of company's total
output, or more than 400,000 tons of products, were
shipped to overseas markets during 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
