<HEADLINE> Poland Eager to Join European Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski said here Monday that Poland was willing to join the
European Union as soon as possible in a bid to consolidate its
economic achievements.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski made the remark at a banquet hosted by Austrian
Federal President Thomas Klestil. Kwasniewski said it was
necessary for Poland to join the EU in order to consolidate
economic and political reforms as well as sustain economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski said that Austria, which will chair the EU in the
second half of the year, would play a significant role in membership
negotiations between the EU and candidate countries such as Poland.
</P>
<P>
Viktor Klima, the Austrian federal chancellor, told the press
after his talk with the visiting Polish president that he would
firmly support the ongoing process of EU enlargement.
</P>
<P>
Klima has suggested that during Austria's chairmanship,
membership negotiations would achieve significant progress.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski ended his one-day official visit to Austria by
delivering a speech to the Austrian Entrepreneur Federation.
</P>
</TEXT>
