<HEADLINE> Thai Government Approves Export Promotion Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 20 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Economic Affairs
Screening Committee has approved in principle a program worth 1.19
billion US dollars to make the country's industrial exports more
competitive.
</P>
<P>
The five-year program is designed to develop and improve
production technology, product design, overseas market access and
industrial pollution.
</P>
<P>
The value the industrial sector adds to primary products
accounts for 29 percent of gross domestic product and generates
annual foreign exchange income of about 70 percent of the
country's total exports. The sector employs more than four million
people.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister Suvit Khunkiti was quoted Tuesday by
local press as saying that Thailand needed an intensive
restructuring to enhance its competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Thai agencies involved in the program include Industry
Ministry, Agriculture and Cooperatives Ministry, Board of
Investment and Science, Technology and Environment Ministry.
</P>
