<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing University to Build Biggest College Library in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 20 (Xinhua) -- A new library at Beijing
University, with a total floor space of 27,000 square meters and 3
million books in stock, will be completed by May, when the
university will celebrate its 100th birth anniversary.
</P>
<P>
By that time, Beijing University will have Asia's biggest
college library, which has a total floor space of 50,000 square
meters, 4,500 seats in reading rooms and more than seven million
books.
</P>
<P>
The new library will feature a style of traditional Chinese
architecture. The latest electronic equipment and automatic
systems will be installed to offer all-around modern services to
readers.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the library started in June of 1996, and its
total investment was 100 million yuan (12 million
U.S. dollars), including 10 million U.S. dollars donated by Li
Ka-shing, a Hong Kong entrepreneur.
</P>
<P>
The current library at Beijing University, established along
with the university, is now the biggest in China's institutions
of higher learning, with 4.3 million books in stock.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
