<DOCNO> XIE19980120.0280 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Record in Tobacco Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, January 20 (Xinhua) -- China's 1997 tobacco exports
hit a record 480 million US dollars, according to information
released at a national tobacco meeting held here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The nation exported 76,000 tons of tobacco, a year-on-year rise
of 22.5 percent, according to Ni Yijin, director of the State
Tobacco Monopoly Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The tobacco sector's pretax profits grew by 8.4 percent to 90
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The sector also introduced steps to upgrade production, with
the average 41.6 kg of tobacco used for each case of cigarettes
falling by 1.6 kg on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the sector has tried to improve its
distribution system, especially in rural areas, with the
industry's profits hitting 510 million yuan, up 4.55 percent
on 1996, according to Ni.
</P>
<P>
China has the world's largest market for tobacco, and
is rapidly emerging as a major exporter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
