<HEADLINE> Russia Supports Multipolarization of the World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
said he backs the idea of building a multipolarized world.
</P>
<P>
Back to work from a two-week vacation, Yeltsin held a short
ceremony on Monday in the Kremlin and received the credentials of
nine new ambassadors to Russia, reported Itar-Tass news agency.
</P>
<P>
Russia sincerely hopes to strengthen world security and stability
and develop cooperation with all countries, said Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
He said Russia attaches great importance to its friendly ties
with the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS), especially the
"alliance" with Belarussia.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin said his country values cooperation with the United
States. However, Russia and the United States are equal partners,
their cooperation should be conducted on an equal basis, he added.
</P>
<P>
Russia also wishes to develop cooperation with Asia-Pacific
countries.
</P>
<P>
On Russia's relationship with European countries, Yeltsin said
the drafting of a Russia-Europe security charter is under way.
</P>
</TEXT>
