<HEADLINE> Farmers' Paintings Encouraged in South China County </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, January 20 (Xinhua) -- The government of Mayang
County in South China's Hunan Province has allocated more than
800,000 yuan to encourage paintings by local farmers.
</P>
<P>
The cultural department of Mayang County has selected more than
700 pupils to receive special painting courses.
</P>
<P>
At present, the county has about 260 farmer artists whose
paintings have won various international prizes.
</P>
<P>
Evolved from paper cutting, cross-stitch work and embroidering,
the farmer paintings of Mayang County are full of local folk
flavors and customs.
</P>
<P>
So far the county has organized 28 paintings expositions.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-six pieces of the farmers' works have been collected by
the State and more than 160 paintings were bought by visitors
from the United States, Canada and some European countries. 
