Committee and the International Labor Organization Monday said
they would work together to promote social justice and elimimate
the use of child labor, according to reports from Lausanne.
</P>
<P>
The two organizations signed a joint agreement for "promoting
social justice and human dignity worldwide" and encourging
activities "which contribute to the elimination of poverty and
child labor."
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by IOC president Juan Antonio
Samaranch and the director general of the International Labor
Office Michel Hansenne. 
</P>
</TEXT>
