<HEADLINE> Morocco Finalise World Cup Warm-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RABAT, January 19 (Xinhua) -- Morocco's coach Henri Michel
revealed the national team's program of warm-up friendlies for the
World Cup finals on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Michel, who coached France to the 1986 World Cup
semi-finals and was in charge of Cameroon at the 1994 finals,
said that he would mainly rely on the forthcoming African Nations
Cup, which starts in Burkina Faso on February 7.
</P>
<P>
Morocco will also play host to France, Belgium and England for
the King Hassan II Cup, which will be played in Casablanca on May
16 and 17 -- the three World Cup finalists confirmed their
participation.
</P>
<P>
Michel noted that apart from a friendly with Chile in Avignon,
France, on June 4 he would base the rest of his team's
preparations on how they fared in the Nations Cup.
</P>
<P>
At the World Cup finals Morocco have been drawn in Group One
along with Brazil, Norway and Scotland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
